-- U.K. Stocks Drop For Fifth Day; FTSE 100 Declines 0.4%
-- B y   S a r a h   J o n e s
-- 2013-03-21T08:35:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-21/u-k-stocks-drop-for-fifth-day-ftse-100-declines-0-4-.html
U.K. stocks declined for a fifth
day, the longest stretch of losses since May.  The benchmark FTSE 100 Index slid 0.6 percent to 6,393.94
at 8:33 a.m. in  London  after opening little changed. The gauge
has lost 2.1 percent in the past five sessions.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
